            "commit": "f3937cc11461814c195d30b4fdf61ac8eca480b0",
            "subject": "LU-0000 llite: improve ACTIVE_WRITER lock handling"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-08 16:14:34.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-08 17:33:15.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 llite: remove LDLM_FL_NO_LRU from ACTIVE_WRITER locks",
        "message": "LU-0000 llite: remove LDLM_FL_NO_LRU from ACTIVE_WRITER locks\n\nRemove the LDLM_FL_NO_LRU flag from ACTIVE_WRITER lock acquisition\nto allow proper lock cancellation and LRU management.\n\nPreviously, ACTIVE_WRITER locks were created with LDLM_FL_NO_LRU\nflag, which prevented them from being added to the LRU list and\ncancelled normally. This caused the server-side active writer\ncount to remain elevated instead of being decremented when locks\nwere released.\n\nThe LDLM_FL_NO_LRU flag is generally undesired for ACTIVE_WRITER\nlocks as it prevents normal lock lifecycle management. With this\nchange, ACTIVE_WRITER locks can now be properly cancelled through\nthe normal LRU mechanism and ldlm_lock_decref_and_cancel() calls.\n\nThis fix works in conjunction with the previous server-side fix\nin mdt_intent_lock_replace() that ensures proper l_conn_export\nsetup for cancellation RPCs.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ief960d47d13c20cf5544b5fc6a4544d23bc08268\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
